
[1]chili

   CHILI, a.

   1. Cool; moderately cold; tending to cause shivering; as the chill
   vapors of night.

   2. Shivering with cold.

   My chill veins freeze with despair.

   3. Cool; distant; formal; dull; not warm, animated or affectionate; as
   a chill reception.

   4. Depressed; dispirited; dejected; discouraged.
